sentences: Simon Nabatov (born 11 January 1959) is a Russian-American jazz pianist.
Nabatov was born in Moscow on 11 January 1959.
He attended a Duke Ellington concert in Moscow in 1971 and his determination to become a jazz musician was reinforced a year later at a Thad Jones–Mel Lewis Orchestra performance.
He attended a Duke Ellington concert in Moscow in 1971 and his determination to become a jazz musician was reinforced a year later at a Thad Jones–Mel Lewis Orchestra performance.
Nabatov and his parents were permitted to leave the Soviet Union in 1979.
Nabatov attended the Juilliard School from 1980 to 1984.
In 1981, he accompanied avant-garde dancer Kazuo Ohno in performances in New York.
In 1984, the magazine Keyboard named him Best Pianist.
He became an American citizen in 1986.
That year, he recorded a trio album, Circle the Line, with bassist Ed Schuller and drummer Paul Motian.
In 1989, he and his German partner settled in Cologne.
Nabatov has taught at several institutions, including the Folkwang Hochschule in Essen (1989–91), the International Jazz and Rock Academy in Remscheid (1991–93), and the Musikhochschule Luzern.
